content: I'm actually planning to shoot some black and white photos with my 1950s-era Canon rangefinder soon, and I was thinking of using some expired Tri-X film I picked up at a thrift store. I've heard that Tri-X is a great film for capturing high-contrast images, but I'm a bit worried about the grain. Do you think I should try developing the film myself, or would it be better to send it to a lab?
